         <abstract>
            <p>This article develops a methodology for analysis of strategies altering the exchange risk position of the firm. The strategies discussed are funds transfers and forward contracts, and combinations of the two. The analysis is presented using various decision criteria: minimum variance, minimax, expected monetary value, and expected utility.</p>
